title: Vincent van Gogh Boxed Note Cards
description:
Cards developed from Vincent van Gogh’s, The Bedroom, 1889; Self-Portrait, 1887; The Poet’s Garden, 1888; Madame Roulin Rocking the Cradle (La berceuse), 1889; Fishing in Spring, the Pont de Clichy (Asnières), 1887 from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

During Vincent van Gogh’s tumultuous career as a painter, he created a revolutionary style characterized by exaggerated forms, a vivid color palette, and loose, spontaneous handling of paint. Although he only actively pursued his art for five years before his death in 1890, his impact has lived on through his works.

  • Card dimensions: 5 x 7 in.
  • Box dimensions: 5.625 x 7.625 x 1.375 in.
  • 20 cards and envelopes; 4 cards each of 5 images.
